This cat is one of the oldest and most recognizable domestic cat types, originating from Thailand. It is known for its striking blue almond-shaped eyes, sleek short coat, and distinct color patterns, with a cream-colored body and darker points on the ears, face, paws, and tail.

These cats are highly social, intelligent, and affectionate. They are vocal, often communicating with a distinctive, melodious voice. Extremely active and playful, they require mental stimulation and interaction. They form strong bonds with their human companions and often become especially attached to one person.

Personality-wise, these cats are curious, adventurous, and sometimes mischievous. They enjoy exploring their environment and may attempt to open doors or cabinets. Despite their independent nature, they thrive on attention and can suffer from loneliness if left alone for extended periods.

With a short coat that requires minimal grooming, regular brushing helps keep it clean and free of tangles. Generally healthy, they may be prone to some specific conditions, such as respiratory issues.

Overall, this cat type is a beloved and charming companion, ideal for those seeking a loyal and interactive feline friend.